Itron, Inc.(Itron), incorporated on December 1, 1977, is a technology company. The Company is the global suppliers of a broad range of standard, advanced, and smart meters and meter communication systems, including networks and communication modules, software and services. The… MoreItron, Inc.(Itron), incorporated on December 1, 1977, is a technology company. The Company is the global suppliers of a broad range of standard, advanced, and smart meters and meter communication systems, including networks and communication modules, software and services. The Company operates in two operating segments: Energy and Water. The Energy operating segment includes its global electricity and gas products. The Water operating segment includes its global water and heat products. The Company’s communications network platform supports robust and standards-based Internet protocol, power-line-carrier, and cellular networks supporting multiple protocols according to its customers' needs around the world.

Itron sold its distribution design business to GeoSpatial Innovations Inc.
Itron, Inc.(Itron), incorporated on December 1, 1977, is a technology company. The Company is the global suppliers of a broad range of standard, advanced, and smart meters and meter communication systems, including networks and communication modules, software and services. The… MoreItron, Inc.(Itron), incorporated on December 1, 1977, is a technology company. The Company is the global suppliers of a broad range of standard, advanced, and smart meters and meter communication systems, including networks and communication modules, software and services. The Company operates in two operating segments: Energy and Water. The Energy operating segment includes its global electricity and gas products. The Water operating segment includes its global water and heat products. The Company’s communications network platform supports robust and standards-based Internet protocol, power-line-carrier, and cellular networks supporting multiple protocols according to its customers' needs around the world.
Itron, Inc.’s Information Technology department supports business objectives that include providing a wide range of utility software solutions. Internal IT services provide day-to-day technology needs of employees.

 The IT department is composed of several smaller units. The units make up IT operations and include human resources information systems, enterprise applications, software development, and business solutions. IT staff members rely on Siebel CRM and PeopleSoft HRMS applications. 

 The department liaises with an IT director who is involved with product development and is responsible for security, testing, and IT quality for the company's software solutions. 

 The IT department has been involved in ongoing server consolidation using VMware and has expanded use of this technology to virtual machines within the company. 





